Use of Hood Island Firing Range is indicated by a display of red flags or red lights. See Byelaws, Practise and Exercise Areas (PEXA) Charts and Annual Notice to Mariners No 5.
Submarines exercise, both surfaced and dived, in the area indicated. A good lookout is to be kept for them when passing through these waters. See Annual Notice to Mariners No 8.

Production platforms and associated structures, including tanker moorings, storage tankers and platforms on pipelines, generally exhibit Mo(U) lights, aircraft obstruction lights, and audible fog signals. Unauthorized navigation is prohibited within 500 metres of all such structures, including storage tankers which can swing about their moorings. Tankers manoeuvring in the vicinity of platforms and moorings should be given a wide berth. For further information see Mariner`s Handbook NP 100.

The Deep Water Route (DW) has been specially surveyed for deep-draught vessels. Mariners must take into account possible changes in depths due to meteorological and other effects. The DW route has been designated by IMO as a two-way route for tankers from Furania Bank to Guysome Shoal. See Admiralty sailing Directions.
To avoid the risk of pollution, all vessels carrying dangerous or toxic cargoes, and all vessels exceeding 500 grt, should avoid the area indicated.
